<div class="page-section page-section--hero">
  <div class="max-width-wrapper">
    <h1 class="page-title">About me...</h1>
    <p id="tidbits" class="about-page__tidbits">A few tidbits:</p>
    <ul aria-labelledby="tidbits" class="about-page__tidbits-list" role="list">
      <li>
        I’ve been working as a front-end developer for the past 7 years,
        building products for both B2C and B2B.
      </li>
      <li>
        My journey into coding started with a year and a half of self-learning.
        This time was filled with perseverance, frustration, and plenty of "What
        am I doing?" moments.
      </li>
      <li>
        Professionally, I've worked extensively with React and its evolving ecosystem, from Redux and class components to hooks, TypeScript, and modern tooling like TanStack Query and Vite. 
      <li>
        Web accessibility is something I care deeply about. With every project,
        I try to dig deeper and build things that are as inclusive and
        user-friendly as possible.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span>
        I also love branching out and experimenting. Lately, that means learning Rust and 
        building <a href="https://github.com/liv7c/nemcss" target="_blank">NemCSS</a>, an open source CSS tooling project built in Rust. And for the past
        three years, I’ve been using Vim and Neovim (editing this
        way makes me happy).
        </span>
      </li>
      <li><span>After being very lucky to live and work in Paris for the past 7 years, I will be starting a new chapter <strong>relocating to Toronto, Ontario in August 2026.</strong></span></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
